* use mstest for web tests and delete artifacts in script

issue.title: nuget push returns InternalServerError three times but succeeds?
issue.body:
I'm having an issue when I push to private Nuget.Server I built and installed on Azure.  I get three error responses back but it indeed does push successfully!?  This get to be a real issue when wanting to push symbols at same time.  I've tried with and without symbols nupkg in same folder.  Deleting has simular problems (but does delete).  Pushing/Deleting to public nuget.org works fine.  I'm using nuget 3.5.0.1938.  Here is the command output ..

nuget push "C:\Users\chammons\Google Drive\GitRepos\vusionpackages\Vusion.Exporter\bin\Release\Vusion.Exporter.1.1.8.28398.nupkg" -source "https://vusionserver.azurewebsites.net/" -ApiKey "hidden-for-security-reasons"
Pushing Vusion.Exporter.1.1.8.28398.nupkg to 'https://vusionnugetserver.azurewebsites.net/'...
  PUT https://vusionnugetserver.azurewebsites.net/api/v2/package/
Using credentials from config. UserName: VusionNuget
  InternalServerError https://vusionnugetserver.azurewebsites.net/api/v2/package/ 1166ms
  PUT https://vusionnugetserver.azurewebsites.net/api/v2/package/
  InternalServerError https://vusionnugetserver.azurewebsites.net/api/v2/package/ 135ms
  PUT https://vusionnugetserver.azurewebsites.net/api/v2/package/
  InternalServerError https://vusionnugetserver.azurewebsites.net/api/v2/package/ 143ms
Response status code does not indicate success: 500 (Package Vusion.Exporter 1.1.8.28398 already exists. The server is configured to not allow overwriting packages that already exist.).

Sever is setup to use basic auth so sources have credentials.
Here is my global nuget.config file ..

```
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<configuration>
  <packageSources>
    <add key="nuget.org" value="https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json" protocolVersion="3" />
    <add key="VusionNuget" value="https://vusionnugetserver.azurewebsites.net/nuget" />
    <add key="VusionNugetPublish" value="https://vusionnugetserver.azurewebsites.net/" />
  </packageSources>
  <disabledPackageSources>
    <add key="VusionNugetPublish" value="false" />
  </disabledPackageSources>
  <packageRestore>
    <add key="enabled" value="True" />
    <add key="automatic" value="True" />
  </packageRestore>
  <bindingRedirects>
    <add key="skip" value="False" />
  </bindingRedirects>
  <packageSourceCredentials>
    <VusionNuget>
      <add key="Username" value="VusionNuget" />
      <add key="ClearTextPassword" value="hidden" />
    </VusionNuget>
    <VusionNugetPublish>
      <add key="Username" value="VusionNuget" />
      <add key="ClearTextPassword" value="hidden" />
    </VusionNugetPublish>
  </packageSourceCredentials>
</configuration>
```

comment.body:
@chammonsvusion Can you get us a fiddler trace for these requests and the error logs from the Azure app/VM that you are hosting this on?

It seems that there is an error being thrown between completion of the operation and the return, and we need a bit more information to track it down. Thanks!
